10.3 Types of Exceptions

                                 Types of Exceptions
                               ↙️                    ↘️
                          User-Defined            Built-in
                          Exception               Exception
                                                ↙️          ↘️
                                            Checked       Unchecked
                                           Exceptions     Exceptions
                                               ⬇️             ⬇️
                               ClassNotFoundException    ArithmeticException
                               InterruptedException      ClassCastException
                               IOException               NullPointer Exception
                               InstantiationException    ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException
                               SQLException              ArrayStoreException
                               FileNotFoundException     IllegalThreadStateException


1. Checked Exceptions: These are exceptions that must be either caught or
                       declared in the method.
2. Unchecked Exceptions: These are exceptions that do not need to be explicitly handled.
